==
A. Prepare Vertica
1. you need to run the Vertica instance: run the script ./start-vertica.sh
2. log on to this container
3. execute the command 
	/opt/vertica/bin/vsql -h localhost docker dbadmin
	Pass: foo123
4. create a table:
	CREATE TABLE public.test(id INT, value VARCHAR);
==

B. Create a flow, which:
1. Fill Vertica with random data:
	a. We generate 100 FlowFile files per second
	b. add each workflow file as a "key" attribute (monotonous increasing integer) and "value" (randomly generated value) (use random() function)
	c. Attributes converted to JSON
	d. JSON stored in the Vertica database


C. Create a flow, which:
1. incrementally retrieves records from the Vertica database in Avro format
2. filters the results (only records with even keys remain)
3. aggregates content to packages of 1000 records each
4. write the result of the aggregation in the HDFS
